For CommonJS and CommonJS-like environments where a proper window is present, execute the factory and get jQuery. For environments that do not have a window with a document (such as Node.js), expose a factory as module.exports. This accentuates the need for the creation of a real window. e.g. var jQuery = require("jquery")(window); See ticket #14549 for more info.
